    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Synthesis, Characterization, Pharmacological Screening and Qsar Analysis of Novel Gallic Acid Derivatives</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Arun Kumar.S</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Synthesis<br />Novel Gallic Acid</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Apr-2011 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">T0028</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A series of novel 2-Aryl-N-(3,4,5-trihtydroxy)-benzamido-4-
thiazolidinones 4a-o and 4-Aryl-3-chloro-N-(3,4,5-trihydroxy)-benzamido-2-
azetidinones 5a-o were synthesized by multistep reaction starting from propyl
gallate. Propyl gallate (1) on reaction with hydrazine hydrate was converted
into galloyl hydrazide (2). The intermediate compound 2 underwent Schiff
reaction with different aromatic aldehydes to yield fifteen Schiff bases 3a-o.
This Schiff bases on intramolecular cyclization with thioglycolic acid yielded
2-Aryl-N-(3,4,5-trihtydroxy)benzamido-4-thiazolidinones 4a-o where as
cyclization with chloroacetyl chloride in presence of triethyl amine in dioxane
yielded 4-Aryl-3-chloro-N-(3,4,5-trihydroxy)-benzamido-2-azetidinones 5ao.
The thiazolidinones and azetidinones were obtained in good yield in the
range of 60-80%. Further the structure of all the synthesized compounds were
confirmed by spectral studies including IR, NMR and Mass spectra.
All the synthesised compounds 4a-o and 5a-o were tested for in vitro
antitubercular activity against Mycobacterium tuberculosis H37Rv using
Microplate alamar blue assay (MABA) method and Minimum inhibitory
concentration (MIC) was determined. The study revealed that, the compounds
4f, 4g and 4o of thiazolidinones and 5f, 5g and 5o of azetidinones which
possess chloro group in benzene ring enhances the activity and showed MIC
values comparable to that of standard drug Isoniazid.
Antimicrobial activity was evaluated for all the synthesized
compounds and MIC was calculated by broth dilution method against the
bacterial strains of Bacillus subtilis, Staphylococcus aureus, Streptococcus
viii
mutans, Escherichia coli, Klebsiella pneumonia and Pseudomonas
aeruginosa. Ciprofloxacin was used as standard for comparison. The
antifungal strains were evaluated against the fungal strains of Candida
albicans and Aspergillus niger. Ketoconazole was used as standard drug. The
compounds 4f, 4g and 4o in thiazolidinone series and 5f, 5g and 5o in the
azetidinone series exhibited excellent antimicrobial activity against all the
bacterial strains and the fungal strains. Other compounds were moderately
active when compared with standard drugs.
The in vitro antioxidant activity was carried out by two methods, i.e.,
DPPH and nitric oxide scavenging methods for all the synthesised
compounds. IC50 values of the compounds were calculated. During the study
it was observed that titled compounds 4e, 4h, 4i, 4k, 4l, 5e, 5h, 5i, 5k and 5l
showed better antioxidant activity when compared to the standard drug
Ascorbic acid, while the other compounds are less active.
QSAR studies were also performed on synthesized compounds 4a-o
and 5a-o against antitubercular and antioxidant activities. Among the
equations generated, the best equations were selected on the basis of various
statistical parameters like standard deviation, F- value, r2, Chance, SPRESS and
Variance. The robustness and applicability of QSAR equations were further
performed using Leave One Out (LOO) cross validation method.
The QSAR report of antitubercular activity for the synthesized
compounds revealed that steric parameter, thermodynamic and electronic
parameters contributes to the activity positively. Among the parameters
Principle Moment of Inertia in X axis (PMI-X), Conolly solvent excluded
volume (Csev), Heat of formation (Hf), Van der Waals force (Vdw) and
Stretch bend energy (Stberg) contributed positively to the activity.
ix
In QSAR report of antioxidant activity, the contributing parameters are
Csev, Principle Moment of Inertia in Y axis (PMI-Y) and Z axis (PMI-Z),
Non Van der Waals force (NVDW), Volume (V), Partition Coefficent (PC),
Critical Temperature (CT) and Molecular Weight (MW). The work definitely
paved a route to design novel compounds of gallic acid derivatives.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/7021">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/7021</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/6855">Ph.D - Thesis  </a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
